internal/pinyin
================

This directory bundles two upstream projects so the build is hermetic
and has no Go module dependency on either:

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
go-pinyin — Hanzi to pinyin converter
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Files:    pinyin.go, phonetic_symbol.go, pinyin_dict.go, doc.go
Source:   https://github.com/mozillazg/go-pinyin
Copyright (c) 2016 mozillazg, 闲耘
License:  MIT (see ./LICENSE)

The source files were copied without modification. The original
PinyinDict (per-character Unihan-derived readings, comma-separated when a
character has more than one) is intact. We added one file of our own,
phrases.go, which is described below.

CLI tooling (cli/), tools (_tools/), tests, examples, and benchmarks
were not vendored.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
phrase-pinyin-data — Chinese phrase → pinyin dictionary
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Files:    data/pinyin.txt, data/overwrite.txt (+ LICENSE, README.md)
Source:   https://github.com/mozillazg/phrase-pinyin-data
Copyright (c) 2017 mozillazg
License:  MIT (see ./data/LICENSE)

pinyin.txt is the curated primary dictionary (~47k entries); overwrite.txt
contains ~900 manual corrections that supersede pinyin.txt at load time.
Both files use the format `<phrase>: <pinyin syllables>`, one entry per
line, comments prefixed with `#`. They are embedded into the binary via
`go:embed` in phrases.go and parsed once on first use.

The other dictionaries shipped by phrase-pinyin-data upstream
(cc_cedict.txt, large_pinyin.txt, zdic_*.txt, di.txt) are not vendored —
they would inflate the binary by ~20MB for marginal coverage gain.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Original code in this directory
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
File:     phrases.go
Author:   Digital Bible Society / transliterate contributors
License:  MIT (same as the rest of this project)

This file glues the two upstream sources together: it loads the embedded
phrase data and exposes LookupPhrase / MaxPhraseRunes, which the
languages/hani package uses to perform longest-match polyphone
disambiguation before falling back to go-pinyin's per-character lookup.
